### The “1906” connection
The year **1906** refers to the **Alaska Native Allotment Act of 1906** — the first U.S. law that gave individual Alaska Natives the legal right to apply for up to **160 acres** of federal land as a restricted (trust) allotment. This was the primary mechanism for Alaska Natives to secure title to traditional use areas before the much larger Alaska Native Claims Settlement Act (ANCSA) of 1971.

